      "name": "Note: Prepare Approval Packet"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Request Approval via Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Hold for Decision · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2",
        "width": 280,
        "height": 232,
        "color": 2
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        642,
        520
      ],
      "id": "2fe6589d-a698-3578-4d55-9d750dff36aa",
      "name": "Note: Request Approval via Slack"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Hold for Decision\n\nPauses the execution until the resume webhook is called — this is the approval/HITL gate.\n\nNext: Approved?",
        "width": 280,
        "height": 232,
        "color": 2
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        966,
        520
      ],
      "id": "d313f720-20a9-5263-3a67-e952b641c5c6",
      "name": "Note: Hold for Decision"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Approved?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.body?.decision || $json.decision }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Apply Approved Change (Notion) · ②→ Record Decline + Notify Requester",
        "width": 280,
        "height": 232,
        "color": 2
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1290,
